<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=14683&amp;p=193053#p193053"><![CDATA[
FCEUX for Windows supports Famicom 4-player. Famicom games for 1 or 2 players treat controller 3 as controller 1 and controller 4 as controller 2.<br /><br />In Config &gt; Input, do this:<br /><ol style="list-style-type: decimal"><li>Change Famicom Expansion Port to 4-Player Adapter </li><li>Change Port 1 to Gamepad and click Configure </li><li>Change Port 2 to Gamepad and click Configure </li></ol>fceux4p.png<br /><br />Speculation I: If the Hori thing does actually support four players, then perhaps it's like the Hudson Multitap: two controllers while strobe is 0 and the other two while strobe is 1.<br /><br />Speculation II: The diagram shows the built-in controllers being disconnected. Perhaps at least input 2 works when built-in controller 2 is internally unplugged. Who can translate the Japanese?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Tue Apr 11, 2017 4:28 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
