<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=14683&amp;p=193038#p193038</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=14683&amp;p=193038#p193038"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Space Race]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=14683&amp;p=193038#p193038"><![CDATA[
There is quite literally <em>no way</em> for an external peripheral connected to the expansion port to put bits in the correct place to be read as player 1 by the CPU.<br /><br />The Famicom expansion port connector provides access <em>only</em> to player 2 ([$4017]&amp;1), player 4 ([$4017]&amp;2), three other pins used for other expansion port devices ([$4017]&amp;$1C), and player 3 ([$4016]&amp;2). There is no connection to player 1 ([$4016]&amp;1).<br /><br />Software could be written to read the extra controllers off one of the available pins that <em>are</em> there, but that requires a software intervention, not a hardware one.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Tue Apr 11, 2017 2:32 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
